Vice President Harris stated that the next step on voting rights is to continue working on it. She mentioned making calls and meeting with people to advocate for the issue. She emphasized the importance of not giving up, as the future of the country's democracy is at stake. Harris urged the United States Senate to pass the voting rights bills before them, and she expressed that resistance will not deter their commitment to getting it done. When asked about her message to Senators Manchin and Sinema, Harris emphasized that all senators have a responsibility to uphold their oath to support and defend the Constitution.